{
  "texts": [
    "KGs provide structured knowledge for decision-making but struggle with natural language nuances and unstructured data [25], [26].",
    "Recent efforts integrate LLMs and KGs to address these limitations [27], [28], combining natural language understanding with structured knowledge.This work introduces Embodied Robotic Control Prompts (ERCPs) and an Embodied Knowledge Graph (EKG) framework incorporating Graph Attention Networks (GATs) and Hamiltonian Paths.",
    "Ps guide LLMs in generating safe task plans by combining human instructions, predefined action primitives, and contextual clarifications.",
    "The EKG framework, enhanced with GATs, prioritizes critical nodes and edges during validation, while Hamiltonian Paths enforce the correct sequence of actions.",
    "This integration addresses challenges in real-time validation, contextual knowledge representation, and logical reasoning, enabling safer and more reliable service robots in dynamic environments."
  ]
}